This documentation describes the DataStax Enterprise for PCF for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF). 
The DataStax Enterprise for PCF enables developers to provision a dedicated DataStax Enterprise (DSE) cluster on-demand to build cloud-scale app.  

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

DataStax Enterprise for PCF enables app developers to create a dedicated DSE cluster to serve their apps.
In its current closed beta period, the DataStax Enterprise for PCF service offers three plans:

+ sample-bronze-plan
+ sample-silver-plan
+ sample-gold-plan

PCF tile administrators can associate different VM types to each plan.
Developers can then use the Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface (cf CLI) to create dedicated instances
of the service plans and bind the instances to their apps.

Creating a DataStax Enterprise for PCF service instance and binding it to an app creates
a database connection from an app to a backend dedicated DSE cluster.
This lets developers use the connection to manipulate data residing on the dedicated DataStax Enterprise Cassandra NoSQL database cluster.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

DataStax Enterprise for PCF lets PCF developers:

* Self-provision a DSE cluster on-demand from three different service plans.
* Connect PCF apps to a dedicated DSE cluster.
* Decommission a DSE cluster.

